  "text": "This gel is atypical by demonstrating significant hardening and cannot be described as a normal gel state as seen for the other materials exceeding LCST when heated. Owing to this hardening of Pluronic ® to form a nanocolloidal glass at slightly larger particle sizes, the dissolution and release of the encapsulated drugs such as procaine hydrochloride could be significantly slowed down. Thus, employing the same type of encapsulation material, but at different concentrations to result in particle size increases, the release characteristics at a set temperature can be markedly influenced [CITATION_1] .",
